e:\n  - no sweep axis is reopened;\n  - all outputs are scorecard-ready;\n  - another worker can see whether the historical anchor ordering still reproduces on the current repo, scene root, and machine.\n\n## Why Not The Other Plausible Options\n\n- Not another occupancy sweep:\n  - the old `occ_refine_v5/v6` runs already established the geometry-vs-PSNR tradeoff and did not beat the shipping anchor on PSNR.\n- Not a full 3DGS-parity optimization run:\n  - that would already be optimization work, not pre-optimization alignment.\n- Not a single-point anchor rerun only:\n  - it would still leave the flat/no-occupancy control missing, so the comparison logic would remain underspecified.\n\n## Experiment Contract\n\n- Repo:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260321_sfc_graphics_repr_01/repo/Auto-claude-code-research-in-sleep`\n- Python:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/envs/flowedit/bin/python`\n- Scene root:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260408_sfc_next_stage_dev02/outputs/3dgs_bear_clean/scene/bear`\n- Image dir:\n  - `images_4`\n- Device contract:\n  - stage for `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=2` only\n- SFC protocol:\n  - `resolution=48`\n  - `brick_size=4`\n  - `sparse_ray_mode=interval_budget`\n  - `interval_budget_power=0.80`\n  - `train_steps=360`\n  - `max_views=16`\n  - `eval_stride=4`\n- Branches:\n  - `max_support_middle`\n  - `mean005_w000`\n  - `mean005_w002`\n- Export path after training:\n  - `payload_export_codec=int8_sym`\n  - `payload_export_backend=compact_zlib`\n\n## Expected Reviewable Outputs\n\nFuture launch outputs are staged to land under:\n\n- `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/outputs/bear_alignment_triplet_gpu2/compare`\n- `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/outputs/bear_alignment_triplet_gpu2/codec/int8_sym`\n\nThe important review files should be:\n\n- compare bundle:\n  - `token_compression_summary.md`\n  - one branch directory per control with:\n    - `stone_horse_scene_fit_metrics.json`\n    - `summary.md`\n    - `mesh_token_diagnostics.md`\n    - `pred_frame_*.png`\n    - `gt_frame_*.png`\n- codec bundle:\n  - `payload_codec_bundle_summary.md`\n  - `token_compression_summary.md`\n  - one branch directory per control with:\n    - `payload_codec_metrics.json`\n    - `reexport_summary.json`\n    - `scene_fit_payload_codec_int8_sym.sfcpack.zlib`\n    - `pred_mesh.ply`\n\n## Launch Recommendation\n\nLaunch:\n\n```bash\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/scripts/run_gpu2_alignment_experiment.sh\n```\n\n## GPU2 Caveat\n\nThis brief does not assert that physical `GPU2` is idle right now. The working-root `README.md` says the first probe on `2026-04-13` found `GPU2` idle, but that is stale by definition. The staged script still hardcodes `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=2`; the launch worker must re-check actual `GPU2` availability immediately before running it.\n"}}
