budget occupancy-refine v5 run has completed successfully:\n  - root: `outputs/benchmarks/dev02_bear_res48_mean005_longbudget_occ_refine_v5_steps2400_gpu45/`\n  - branches: `w0.020`, `w0.022`, `w0.026`, `w0.030`\n  - objective: probe the `w0.02 -> w0.03` mid-band stability with medium long-budget regime\n\n## Key Findings from V5 Sweep\n\n- **bear long-budget mean005 w0.02 codec baseline**: PSNR 14.9331, Mesh 3.3612, Codec 22.19 KiB, Render 0.0237s (per `dev02_bear_res48_mean005_longbudget_occ_refine_v6_steps2400_gpu01/payload_codec_bundle_summary`)\n- **bear long-budget mean005 w0.0200**: PSNR 14.7627, Mesh 3.3678, Codec 19.29 KiB\n- **bear long-budget mean005 w0.0220**: PSNR 14.7711, Mesh 3.3413, Codec 19.23 KiB  \n- **bear long-budget mean005 w0.0260**: PSNR 14.7913, Mesh 3.3535, Codec 19.15 KiB\n- **bear long-budget mean005 w0.0300**: PSNR 14.7990, Mesh 3.2995, Codec 19.11 KiB\n\n## Interpretation\n\n- **PSNR leadership still belongs to the codec baseline**: 14.9331 dB vs 14.7990 dB for w0.0300, so the sweep has not caught up on image quality.\n- PSNR within the sweep improves monotonically (14.76 → 14.80 dB), but the entire range remains ≈0.13 dB below the codec baseline.\n- Mesh quality and codec sidecar size peak at w0.0300 (3.2995 Chamfer, 19.11 KiB), showing clear geometry/token gains.\n- Render times currently regress for w0.0300 (0.0784 s) compared with both the codec baseline (0.0237 s) and the w0.0200 branch (0.0348 s).\n- All runs maintain identical storage ratio (16.42x).\n- Codec bundle sizes decrease slightly with higher occupancy weights, but PSNR parity is now the gating metric.\n\n## Strategic Decision\n\nHold the promotion. `outputs/visual_review_20260324.md` now documents that the occupancy-refine sweep still loses to the w0.02 codec baseline on PSNR and render time, so the stable branch remains the codec baseline until a higher-quality export is demonstrated.\n\n## Next Frontier\n\n- Run a codec-aware refine (or exporter tweak) whose explicit 