/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/.codex/sessions/2026/04/13/rollout-2026-04-13T08-18-30-019d85eb-b617-7712-aabe-90f856a1333b.jsonl:168:{"timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:35:41.164Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"call_FmBCjk66Gofxl7qKu7sK0SKU","name":"apply_patch","input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/input/next_alignment_experiment_brief.md\n+# Next Alignment Experiment Brief\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+Run a small one-GPU SFC control bundle on `bear` that refreshes the three comparison points that matter before any new optimization work:\n+\n+1. `max-support middle` as the PSNR-leaning legacy control\n+2. `mean005 w0.00` as the explicit flat / no-occupancy control\n+3. `mean005 w0.02` as the shipping SFC anchor\n+\n+Then re-export all three branches with the same delivered payload path used in prior SFC scorecards: `int8_sym + compact_zlib`.\n+\n+## Why This Is The Most Defensible Next Step\n+\n+- The `2026-04-08` wave already closed the missing `3DGS` clean control:\n+  - `outputs/3dgs_bear_clean/metrics_summary.md` reports `25.4712 dB` PSNR and a completed `20000`-iteration baseline.\n+- What remains unclear is not another optimization frontier. It is the SFC comparison contract:\n+  - the current shipping anchor in `outputs/sfc_anchor_control/anchor_manifest.md` is historical / repacked evidence, not a fresh current-run control;\n+  - the scorecard still has no explicit flat-control bundle;\n+  - the old optimization notes already say not to chase another near-flat probe or reopen blind sweeps.\n+- The old `bear` long-budget compare already identifies the exact three points that define the comparison logic:\n+  - `max-support middle`: best PSNR among the old SFC controls (`15.5172`);\n+  - `mean005 w0.00`: smallest-byte / no-occupancy control (`14.9519` PSNR, worse mesh);\n+  - `mean005 w0.02`: shipping geometry/storage anchor (`14.9331` PSNR, `3.3612` mesh Chamfer).\n+- Re-running just these three branches is small, controllable, and directly reviewable:\n+  - no sweep axis is reopened;\n+  - all outputs are scorecard-ready;\n+  - another worker can see whether the historical anchor ordering still reproduces on the current repo, scene root, and machine.\n+\n+## Why Not The Other Plausible Options\n+\n+- Not another occupancy sweep:\n+  - the old `occ_refine_v5/v6` runs already established the geometry-vs-PSNR tradeoff and did not beat the shipping anchor on PSNR.\n+- Not a full 3DGS-parity optimization run:\n+  - that would already be optimization work, not pre-optimization alignment.\n+- Not a single-point anchor rerun only:\n+  - it would still leave the flat/no-occupancy control missing, so the comparison logic would remain underspecified.\n+\n+## Experiment Contract\n+\n+- Repo:\n+  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260321_sfc_graphics_repr_01/repo/Auto-claude-code-research-in-sleep`\n+- Python:\n+  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/envs/flowedit/bin/python`\n+- Scene root:\n+  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260408_sfc_next_stage_dev02/outputs/3dgs_bear_clean/scene/bear`\n+- Image dir:\n+  - `images_4`\n+- Device contract:\n+  - stage for `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=2` only\n+- SFC protocol:\n+  - `resolution=48`\n+  - `brick_size=4`\n+  - `sparse_ray_mode=interval_budget`\n+  - `interval_budget_power=0.80`\n+  - `train_steps=360`\n+  - `max_views=16`\n+  - `eval_stride=4`\n+- Branches:\n+  - `max_support_middle`\n+  - `mean005_w000`\n+  - `mean005_w002`\n+- Export path after training:\n+  - `payload_export_codec=int8_sym`\n+  - `payload_export_backend=compact_zlib`\n+\n+## Expected Reviewable Outputs\n+\n+Future launch outputs are staged to land under:\n+\n+- `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/outputs/bear_alignment_triplet_gpu2/compare`\n+- `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/aris_sandboxes/20260413_sfc_dev01_alignment_wave/outputs/bear_alignment_triplet_gpu2/codec/int8_sym`\n+\n+The important review files should 