/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_remote_homes/relay3/.codex/sessions/2026/03/27/rollout-2026-03-27T20-30-45-019d30fe-000c-70f2-b409-50b41bb0aaf6.jsonl:115:{"timestamp":"2026-03-27T20:33:19.616Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_KcSvsNvEaqVhNN0iQzmsYaus","output":"Command: /bin/bash -lc 'for f in /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/notes/scheme2_dense_voxel_rework.md /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/notes/scheduler_and_volc_probe.md /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/configs/baseline_strictdc_r1024_b1024_2gpu.yaml; do if [ -f \"$f\" ]; then printf '\"'===== %s =====\\\\n' \\\"\"'$f\"; sed -n '\"'1,260p' \\\"\"'$f\"; printf '\"'\\\\n'; fi; done\"\nChunk ID: af86f5\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 5831\nOutput:\n===== /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/notes/scheme2_dense_voxel_rework.md =====\n# Scheme 2 Dense Voxel Rework\n\n## Scope\n\nThis note designs the dense face-through-voxel representation for the Trellis2-reuse mesh VAE wave under `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff`.\n\nInspected inputs:\n\n- `artistic_mesh_vae/data/build_quantized_cache.py`\n- `artistic_mesh_vae/data/common.py`\n- `artistic_mesh_vae/data/dataset.py`\n- `artistic_mesh_vae/models/scvae.py`\n- `artistic_mesh_vae/evaluation/mesh_utils.py`\n- `sandboxes/20260314_topology_probe/*`\n- `sandboxes/20260316_artistic_mesh_cls/cache_r1024_resolve_10k/*`\n- `/shared-dev/ruocheng_data/training_pool_current_latest.csv.gz`\n\nKey facts from the current code and artifacts:\n\n- The current cache is strictly one token per face, anchored at the face centroid voxel, with `coords`, `feats` `(N, 9)`, `bin_indices` `(N, 9)`, face adjacency arrays, and a per-sample scalar `max_offset`.\n- The current `10k` cache under `sandboxes/20260316_artistic_mesh_cls/cache_r1024_resolve_10k` cached `9,826` samples, failed on `174/10,000`, and needed `3,958,490` collision relocations at `resolution=1024`.\n- The current cache stores `bin_indices` as `int64` and also stores duplicate float `feats`; that is acceptable for the sparse face-anchor baseline but too wasteful for a dense scheme.\n- The topology probe on `sandboxes/20260314_topology_probe/full52_summary_tight_bbox.json` found `1,031,408` faces landing in multi-face voxels across the 52-case set, with `max_faces_per_voxel=933` and `max_components_in_voxel=794`; this confirms that centroid ownership is too sparse, but it also confirms that raw multi-face occupancy is highly ambiguous.\n- The latest training pool file currently contains `564,714` rows after filtering `ready_now == True`, `training_tier == strict_double_clean`, and excluding `source_dataset in {ABO, 3D-FUTURE}`. In the current snapshot all retained rows are from `zhihao_v005_plus_dino`, and `recommended_split` is still `train`, so a frozen explicit train/val split must be created for fair comparison.\n\n## Recommendation Summary\n\nUse a dense one-token-per-occupied-voxel representation, not multi-token packing.\n\n- Each triangle activates every voxel whose cube intersects the triangle.\n- Each occupied voxel stores the voxel-center-anchored vectors to the triangle's three vertices.\n- If multiple faces compete for one voxel, choose a single owner face.\n  - Use deterministic nearest-plane selection for generic overlaps.\n  - Use deterministic hash-based random selection only for true edge/vertex boundary competition, to satisfy the requested random boundary assignment without making the whole cache nondeterministic.\n- Add two binary topology channels and heads:\n  - `is_edge_or_vertex`\n  - `is_open_boundary_edge`\n- Drop face adjacency arrays from the dense cache MVP.\n- Do not keep the current per-sample compressed `.npz` format as the full-training format. Keep `.npz` only for debug/smoke caches; use mmap-friendly shard arrays for real training.\n\n## Proposed End-to-End Data Schema\n\n### Token definition\n\nFor one retained `(voxel, face)` pair:\n\n- Anchor:\n  - `c = (coord + 0.5) / resolution`\n- Geometry target:\n  - `o = [v0 - c, v1 - c, v2 - c]`\n  - `o` is always in `[-1, 1]` per axis after the existing unit-cube normalization, so dense scheme 2 should use a fixed offset range and should not keep `max_offset`.\n- Topology targets:\n  - `is_edge_or_vertex = 1` if any of the triangle's three edges intersects the voxel AABB\n  - `is_open_boundary_edge = 1` if any open boundary edge of the assigned face intersects the voxel AABB\n\n### Training storage schema\n\nRecommended production layout: shard arrays plus a CSV manifest.\n\n```text\ncache_root/\n  manifest.csv\n  shard_0000/\n    coords.npy            # uint16 [T, 3]\n    geom_bins.npy         # uint16 [T, 9]   with num_bins=1024\n    topo_flags.npy        # uint8  [T, 2]   columns: edge_or_vertex, open_boundary\n    sample_ptr.npy        # int64  [S + 1]\n    sample_manifest.csv   # S rows with record_id, sample_id, mesh_path, face_count, token_count, shard_id, begin, end\n    stats.json\n```\n\nDerived on load, not stored:\n\n- `feats`: float32/float16 decoded from `geom_bins`\n- `gt_offsets`: same decoded geometry midpoints\n- `coords`: cast to `int32` for sparse ops\n\nDebug-only fields for smoke caches:\n\n- `owner_face_local.npy` or `owner_face_local` in `.npz`\n- `winner_mode.npy` with enum values like `single`, `nearest_plane`, `random_boundary`\n- `collision_stats_json`\n\nFields to remove from the dense cache MVP:\n\n- `feats` as a stored float array\n- `max_offset`\n- `adj_fi`, `adj_fj`, `adj_vi`, `adj_vj`\n\n### Dtypes\n\n- `coords`: `uint16`\n  - `1024` fits comfortably; current `int32` is unnecessary on disk.\n- `geom_bins`: `uint16`\n  - `1024` bins fit; current `int64` is unnecessarily expensive.\n- `topo_flags`: `uint8`\n- `sample_ptr`: `int64`\n\n## Preprocessing Pipeline\n\n### Stage 1: Freeze the manifest and split\n\nCurrent `artistic_mesh_vae/data/build_candidate_manifest.py` is not suitable for this wave because it still reads ABO and 3D-FUTURE inputs.\n\nUse a new manifest builder for scheme 2 that reads:\n\n- `/shared-dev/ruocheng_data/training_pool_current_latest.csv.gz`\n\nRequired row filter:\n\n- `ready_now == True`\n- `training_tier == \"strict_double_clean\"`\n- `source_dataset not in {\"ABO\", \"3D-FUTURE\"}`\n\nRequired split policy:\n\n- Materialize an explicit split once and reuse it for all four runs.\n- Do not depend on `recommended_split` from the CSV for this wave.\n- Store `train_ids.txt` and `val_ids.txt` under `sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/`.\n\n### Stage 2: Mesh load and normalization\n\nReuse the current mesh normalization logic from `artistic_mesh_vae/data/common.py`:\n\n- load mesh\n- collapse scene to one mesh\n- normalize to the current unit-cube convention\n\nPrecompute once per mesh:\n\n- normalized vertices\n- triangle index array\n- per-face normals\n- per-face voxel AABB bounds\n- undirected edge table and per-edge face counts\n- per-face bitmask of which of its three edges are open boundary edges\n\n### Stage 3: Dense triangle-to-voxel hit generation\n\nThis is the hot path. It must not be written as Python loops over faces or candidate voxels.\n\nRecommended implementation:\n\n- Use chunked `torch` on GPU for the rasterizer because the available environment has `torch 1.13.1+cu116` and does not have `numba`.\n- For each face chunk:\n  - compute integer voxel AABB min/max\n  - compute per-face candidate counts `nx * ny * nz`\n  - flatten candidate voxel generation with prefix sums and `repeat_interleave`\n  - run a fully vectorized triangle-AABB overlap test on all candidate `(face, voxel)` pairs in the chunk\n\nThe overlap test should be conservative and exact enough for voxel ownership. The standard triangle-box SAT test is appropriate here.\n\nMandatory output of this stage:\n\n- `hit_voxel_coord`\n- `hit_face_index`\n- `hit_voxel_key`\n- `plane_abs_distance_to_voxel_center`\n\n### Stage 4: Topology flags on hits\n\nFor every `(face, voxel)` hit, compute:\n\n- `is_edge_or_vertex`\n  - `1` if any triangle edge segment intersects the voxel AABB\n- `is_open_boundary_edge`\n  - `1` if any open boundary edge segment of that face intersects the voxel AABB\n\nThis should be computed in the same chunked torch pass as the rasterizer or immediately after it, still batched and vectorized.\n\n### Stage 5: Resolve competing faces per voxel\n\nOne token must survive per voxel.\n\nRecommended winner rule:\n\n1. If a voxel has exactly one hit, keep it.\n2. If a voxel has multiple hits and at least one candidate is not an edge/vertex hit, keep the candidate with the smallest absolute point-to-plane distance from voxel center to triangle plane.\n3. If all competing candidates are edge/vertex hits, select one randomly with a deterministic hash of `(record_id, voxel_key, face_index)`.\n\nWhy this rule:\n\n- It satisfies the requested random assignment on boundary competition.\n- It avoids poisoning the whole dataset with nondeterministic ownership.\n- It is still cheap to implement with grouped reductions after sorting by `voxel_key`.\n\nPrecompute and store per-sample stats:\n\n- `face_count`\n- `token_count`\n- `token_multiplier = token_count / face_count`\n- `multi_face_voxel_count_before_owner`\n- `random_boundary_wins`\n- `nearest_plane_wins`\n- `max_faces_per_voxel_before_owner`\n- `edge_or_vertex_token_frac`\n- `open_boundary_token_frac`\n\n### Stage 6: Quantize geometry and write shards\n\nFor surviving tokens:\n\n- compute absolute vertex offsets from voxel center\n- quantize with fixed range `[-1, 1]`\n- store `geom_bins` as `uint16`\n- store `topo_flags` as `uint8`\n- append into shard arrays\n\nThe dense scheme should not keep a per-sample `max_offset`. Fixed-range quantization makes the cache smaller and the decode path simpler.\n\n## What Must Be Precomputed\n\nPrecompute once during cache build:\n\n- normalized mesh vertices and faces\n- open boundary edge map\n- face normals\n- dense voxel ownership result\n- token-level `coords`\n- token-level `geom_bins`\n- token-level `topo_flags`\n- per-sample `token_count`\n- per-sample preprocess stats\n- explicit train/val ID lists for the wave\n\nDo not precompute for the production cache:\n\n- float `feats`\n- float `gt_offsets`\n- token-expanded adjacency arrays\n\n## Where Vectorization / CUDA / Torch Ops Are Mandatory\n\nMandatory compiled or batched paths:\n\n- dense triangle-to-voxel hit generation\n- triangle-edge/AABB tests for topology flags\n- grouped ownership reduction by `voxel_key`\n- decoder-side vertex decode and triangle/edge dedupe\n\nAcceptable to keep in ordinary Python:\n\n- one loop over meshes\n- one loop over coarse face chunks\n- manifest filtering and shard bookkeeping\n\nNot acceptable in the hot path:\n\n- Python loops over candidate voxels\n- Python loops over all hits to resolve owners\n- Python loops over decoded tokens during reconstruction\n\n## Storage Layout: `npz` vs Sharded Arrays\n\n### `npz` compressed\n\nPros:\n\n- matches the current code\n- easy to debug\n\n===== /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/notes/scheduler_and_volc_probe.md =====\n# Scheduler And Volc Probe\n\nProbe time: 2026-03-17 around 08:40Z.\n\n## Current machine probe\n\nHost probed: `di-20260312031430-7n4sm`\n\nGPU snapshot from `nvidia-smi` on this host:\n\n- `GPU 0`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `21970 / 81920 MiB`, `40%` util\n- `GPU 1`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `66250 / 81920 MiB`, `99%` util\n- `GPU 2`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `69029 / 81920 MiB`, `100%` util\n- `GPU 3`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `42505 / 81920 MiB`, `100%` util\n- `GPU 4`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `38719 / 81920 MiB`, `87%` util\n- `GPU 5`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `7 / 81920 MiB`, `0%` util\n- `GPU 6`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `42243 / 81920 MiB`, `98%` util\n- `GPU 7`: `NVIDIA A800-SXM4-80GB`, `42245 / 81920 MiB`, `100%` util\n\nLikely safe allocations right now:\n\n- Safe: `GPU 5` only, for a single-GPU smoke check or cache/preflight task.\n- Not safe for fair 2-GPU training: any pair involving `GPU 0` through `GPU 4`, `GPU 6`, or `GPU 7`.\n- Not safe for the requested 4-way comparison: this host does not currently expose even one clean 2-GPU pair.\n\nProcess accounting note:\n\n- `nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps` showed several stale `[Not Found]` PIDs.\n- `nvidia-smi pmon -c 1` did not show live processes.\n- The safer scheduling signal on this host is still the GPU memory and utilization snapshot above; it does not support a fair fresh 2-GPU allocation except maybe `GPU 5` plus a contested partner, which is not acceptable for this comparison.\n\n## Dev-machine reachability\n\n`dev-intern-02` is not immediately usable from this shared environment:\n\n- `getent hosts dev-intern-02` returned nothing.\n- `ssh -o BatchMode=yes -o ConnectTimeout=5 dev-intern-02 hostname` failed with `Could not resolve hostname dev-intern-02`.\n\nHistorical dev-machine artifacts do exist, but they are not a live availability proof:\n\n- Previous 2-GPU fallback script: `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260316_pc_dev01_subagent_orchestration/scripts/run_baseline_r1024_dropcase_k1_10k.sh`\n- Historical runtime notes on `dev-intern-01`: `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260316_pc_dev01_subagent_orchestration/docs/runtime_status.md`\n\nConclusion on dev machines now:\n\n- 4 parallel 2-GPU runs are not currently possible from the capacity I can verify.\n- I can verify only one clean local GPU on the current host.\n- I cannot verify `dev-intern-02` reachability at all from here.\n\n## Volc CLI state\n\n`volc` is not on `PATH`, but it is already installed locally:\n\n- CLI binaries: `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/.volc/bin/volc`, `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/.volc/bin/mlp`\n- Unpacked bundle: `