U fragmentation is preventing immediate placement\n- Older jobs on 2026-03-16 in the same queue often never started and were stopped with quota/fragmentation messages.\n\nConclusion:\n\n- Volc is ready enough to submit jobs now.\n- Volc is not \"start immediately without queue delay\" right now.\n- The current blocker is queue placement and GPU fragmentation, not CLI install or missing credentials.\n\n## Existing 8-GPU template status\n\nInside this project I found reusable launchers, but not a ready-made single-node 8-GPU Volc submission template:\n\n- Single training job inside an allocated platform worker:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/artistic_mesh_vae/launch/run_train_platform.sh`\n  - relevant config fields it sets:\n    - `trainer.accelerator=gpu`\n    - `trainer.devices=${MLP_WORKER_GPU:-gpu_count}`\n    - `trainer.num_nodes=1`\n    - `trainer.strategy=ddp` when GPU count `> 1`\n- Per-run detached launcher that accepts an explicit GPU CSV:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/artistic_mesh_vae/launch/run_train_detached.sh`\n  - relevant config fields it sets:\n    - `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=<gpu_csv>`\n    - `trainer.devices=<len(gpu_csv)>`\n    - `trainer.num_nodes=1`\n    - `trainer.strategy=ddp` when GPU count `> 1`\n\nProject-local finding:\n\n- There is no existing project-local Volc YAML or shell entrypoint for the exact \"one 8-GPU node hosting four parallel 2-GPU runs\" pattern.\n\nClosest reusable external template in the same workspace:\n\n- YAML generator:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/zoom-in-render-dino-classfier/sandboxes/20260316_volc_dino_speed_probe/write_volc_dino_benchmark_yaml.py`\n- Example 1-node YAML:\n  - `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/zoom-in-render-dino-classfier/sandboxes/20260316_volc_dino_speed_probe/yamls/zoom_dino_volc_single_full_overnight_20260316_1n.yaml`\n\nFields worth reusing from that template:\n\n- `ResourceQueueName: \"train-intern\"`\n- `TaskRoleSpecs[0].RoleReplicas: 1`\n- `TaskRoleSpecs[0].Flavor: \"ml.hpcpni2l.28xlarge\"`\n- `Storages` mount for:\n  - `Vepfs` at `/dev_vepfs/rc_wu` with `VepfsId: \"vepfs-cnsh40279a6c9ba2\"`\n  - `TosFuse` at `/shared-dev`\n\nImportant operational point:\n\n- `run_train_platform.sh` will use all visible GPUs for one training job.\n- The correct primitive for the requested 4-way fair split on one 8-GPU node is `run_train_detached.sh` invoked four times with `gpu_csv` values `0,1`, `2,3`, `4,5`, and `6,7`.\n\n## Exact risks\n\n- Current dev-machine capacity does not support 4 fresh 2-GPU runs.\n- `dev-intern-02` is not resolvable from this shared environment.\n- Volc 8-GPU queue placement is currently fragmented; an immediate start is not guaranteed.\n- No project-local 8-GPU sweep entrypoint or YAML exists yet.\n- `mlp devinstance` permissions are insufficient, so I cannot use the CLI to inspect alternate dev-instance states or queues.\n- I did not find a confirmed `SWANLAB_API_KEY_FILE` path in the workspace search; that path must be filled in before launch.\n- Older notes show the older `volc ml_task` path was flaky or timed out; prefer `mlp job create`, not the older `volc ml_task submit` path.\n\n## Exact next commands for a single-node 8-GPU submission\n\nThese commands are the cleanest next path if the four run configs already exist and the goal is one Volc worker with four detached 2-GPU runs inside it.\n\nFirst, expose the local CLI:\n\n```bash\nexport PATH=/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/.volc/bin:$PATH\n```\n\nThen write an entry script under this task sandbox:\n\n```bash\ncat > /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel/ops/mesh_vae_4way_entry.sh <<'SH'\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nPROJECT_ROOT=/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/trellis2_michelangelo_bakeoff\nTASK_ROOT=$PROJECT_ROOT/sandboxes/20260317_mesh_vae_parallel\nLOG_ROOT=$TASK_ROOT/logs_volc_4way\nmkdir -p \"$LOG_ROOT\"\n\nexport SWANLAB_API_KEY_FILE=\"${SWANLAB_API_KEY_FILE:?set SWANLAB_API_KEY_FILE}\"\n\n\"$PROJECT_ROOT/artistic_mesh_vae