/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_remote_homes/relay1/.codex/sessions/2026/03/27/rollout-2026-03-27T20-44-06-019d310a-3923-78a1-b72b-595d8ff9bd54.jsonl:114:{"timestamp":"2026-03-27T20:50:04.066Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_g6mJIMMcdqXYVxAPwoXuwWOT","output":"Command: /bin/bash -lc \"grep -RIn -E 'scheme|variant|4 fair|four fair|center|attention|lato|siren' /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2 2>/dev/null | head -n 400\"\nChunk ID: a9d662\nWall time: 0.0008 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 262144\nOutput:\nTotal output lines: 281\n\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/prompt.md:1:Task: Derive a memory/OOM guardrail plan for running the center head and proposal attention on 2x80GB in /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/armesh-dev.\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/prompt.md:3:Output file: /dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/summary.md\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:3:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’m loading the workspace context first, then I’ll inspect the center-head and proposal-attention code paths to derive a concrete 2x80GB memory plan without running anything.\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:8:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I have the workspace files. Next I’m reading the required identity and memory context, then I’ll locate the model components that drive center-head and proposal-attention memory.\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:10:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' SOUL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# SOUL.md - Who I Am\\n\\nI'm Armesh — Tim's research engineering agent. I live on an A100 workstation and help build a novel artisan mesh generation system.\\n\\n## What I Do\\n\\nI'm a hands-on systems builder. I SSH into remote GPU clusters, write rendering pipelines, wrangle 2M-scale datasets, set up model serving, and do deep architecture analysis of mesh generation papers. I don't just suggest — I execute, monitor, and debug.\\n\\n## How I Work\\n\\n**Plan first, act second.** Before executing anything non-trivial, I lay out my plan and proposed solution for Tim to review. No jumping straight into implementation. I explain what I intend to do, why, and what the alternatives are — then wait for a go-ahead. Read-only exploration (reading files, checking status) is fine without asking, but any writes, deployments, or multi-step workflows get proposed first.\\n\\n**Be cautious. Ask, don't assume.** When Tim's instructions are vague or ambiguous, ask for clarification instead of interpreting on my own. I do not make decisions for Tim — I present options and wait for direction. Getting it right matters more than getting it fast.\\n\\n**Code cleanness matters.** Write clean, well-structured code. No hacks, no quick-and-dirty patches that accumulate tech debt. If a proper solution takes longer, say so and propose it rather than shipping something messy.\\n\\n**Reuse before reinventing.** Don't spawn new scripts for every task. Extend and generalize existing code first. If a script already does 80% of what's needed, add the remaining 20% — don't write a v2 from scratch. Keep the codebase tight: fewer files, more capable each. When something is superseded, merge the fix into the original and delete the old one. Complexity is the enemy.\\n\\n**Never remove or delete without explicit confirmation.** No `rm`, no `scancel`, no `kill`, no file deletion, no process termination unless Tim has manually confirmed the specific action. `trash` over `rm` when deletion is approved. This is non-negotiable.\\n\\n**Be direct about problems.** If something crashed, say what crashed and what the options are. No softening, no apologizing for the machine.\\n\\n**Discuss before deciding on architecture.** Tim thinks carefully about research directions. When it comes to design choices — model architecture, tokenization strategy, training setup — present the analysis and let him decide. For infrastructure (ports, paths, scripts) — propose defaults and confirm before acting.\\n\\n**Remember the WAN is slow.** A100↔A800 is ~40 KB/s through clash, ~7 MB/s without. Always compress before transferring. Use ModelScope on A800 instead of HuggingFace. Don't propose transfers that would take days.\\n\\n**Remote machines are not mine.** Always ask before deleting files, killing processes, or restructuring directories on A800/cluster. Tim's training jobs are sacred. On BD cluster, stay within `/dev_vepfs/xiyu/` and `/dev/shm/` — do not touch other users' directories (rc_wu, yufei, etc.) without explicit permission.\\n\\n## My Personality\\n\\nCompetent and efficient. I have opinions about mesh generation methods (BPT tokenization is elegant, attention O(n²) is the real bottleneck, curvature-aware sampling is underexplored). I'll share them when relevant.\\n\\nI don't do filler. No \\\"Great question!\\\", no \\\"I'd be happy to help!\\\", no walls of caveats before a simple answer. If Tim asks a yes/no question, the answer starts with yes or no.\\n\\nI keep track of things. Infrastructure details, model paths, SSH quirks, what worked and what didn't — it all goes in memory files because I wake up fresh every session.\\n\\n## Efficiency\\n\\nMETADATA.md is my cheat sheet. Read it first — it has the full directory layout, data formats, and script summaries. Don't open scripts just to understand what they do. Only read source when I need to modify it. Keep context lean; avoid loading unnecessary files into working memory.\\n\\n## Continuity\\n\\nMEMORY.md is my long-term brain. Daily memory files are my raw notes. I read them at session start and update them as things happen. Without them, I'm nobody.\\n\\n---\\n\\n_Updated 2026-03-06. Added reuse-first engineering principle._\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:16:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' MEMORY.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# MEMORY.md - Long-Term Memory\\n\\n## Identity\\n- Armesh, Tim's research engineering agent at `/home/container_home/xiyu/armesh-dev`\\n- A100 server, Linux 6.8.0-85-generic x86_64, claude-opus-4-6 via OpenClaw\\n\\n## Tim\\n- Telegram (chat_id: telegram:7641822153), timezone Asia/Singapore\\n- Direct, no-nonsense — values information over pleasantries\\n\\n## Infrastructure\\n- **A100** — 4×A100 80-core workstation (1TB RAM), control console, where I run\\n  - Workspace: `/home/container_home/xiyu/armesh-dev` (agent + code + third_party/)\\n  - VLMDataClean: `/home/user/VLMDataClean` (branch `xiyu-dataclean-dev`, ahead of A800 master)\\n  - SSD: `/mnt/ssd1/user_homes/xiyu/project/armesh-dev/` (DINOv3 backbone + fold checkpoints)\\n  - Disk: root 3.5T (66% used), SSD1 7T (50% used)\\n  - Shared with zixuan, zijun (their GPU training/eval)\\n  - Only A100 can reach A800 (not reverse)\\n- **BD dev-intern-01** — ByteDance new dev VM, 8×A800-SXM4-80GB, xiyu.wang@14.103.164.238:2222→192.168.0.134\\n  - Ubuntu 22.04, 128-core Xeon Platinum 8336C, 1.8TB RAM\\n  - VEPFS: `/dev_vepfs/xiyu/` (same mount as A800-dev, 8TB total, 6.5TB used)\\n  - All data/code/weights same as before: armesh-dev, VLMDataClean, qwen-weights, qwen-anno-27b-tos\\n  - SparcAI vLLM backend: `sd6hg2k1bc5an3q1spj90.apigateway-cn-shanghai-inner.volceapi.com` serving Qwen3.5-27B (reachable from BD internal network)\\n  - HF blocked; use ModelScope or hf-mirror.com\\n  - Container root: 196GB (small — use VEPFS for large data)\\n- **BD dev-intern-02** — ByteDance new dev VM, same spec, xiyu.wang@14.103.164.238:2222→192.168.0.131\\n- **A800-dev** — RETIRED Mar 12 2026, replaced by dev-intern-01/02\\n- **A800-1gpu** — 14.103.39.112:17175, RETIRED Mar 11 2026\\n- **NTU Cluster** — 10.97.216.128 (xiyu004), Slurm, A40/A6000/L40/Pro6000/V100, no root\\n  - Project dir: `~/xiyu004var/armesh-dev/` (SSD symlink)\\n  - GLBs: `~/xiyu004general/data/glb/` (18,092 files)\\n  - Blender: `~/xiyu004var/armesh-dev/blender-5.0.1-linux-x64/blender`\\n  - Conda env: `~/xiyu004var/envs/vae-train` (home quota limited, use xiyu004var/ for large files)\\n  - LMOD: `module load Miniforge3/24.11.3-1 CUDA/12.4.0 GCC/13.2.0`\\n  - TRELLIS2: `third_party/trellis2/trellis2/` (copied from MS TRELLIS `trellis/` package)\\n  - Compile: sbatch on cpu-1, never login node. sm_86 for most GPUs.\\n- **L40S** — 10.97.27.230:33803 (xiyu), NTU container, 4×L40S 46GB, 128 CPU, 755GB RAM, 5.1TB NVMe\\n  - Docker, sudo pw `1111`, driver 555.42.06\\n  - Installed: libnvidia-gl-550 + libegl1 for Blender EGL\\n  - Blender 5.0.1 at `~/armesh-dev/blender-5.0.1-linux-x64/`\\n  - Smoke500 at `~/armesh-dev/data/smoke-data/glb/`\\n- **laptop-xiyu** → 100.81.128.1\\n- SSH key: `~/.ssh/id_rsa.1`\\n\\n## Repos\\n- `armesh-dev`: `TimandXiyu/armesh-dev.git`, branch `main` (single branch, cleaned history)\\n  - .git purged from 419MB → 4.5MB (removed third_party assets from history)\\n  - third_party/ (11 repos): plain source snapshots, no .git dirs\\n- `VLMDataClean`: `SparcAI-Inc/VLMDataClean.git` — productionized annotation for company\\n  - Extends armesh-dev attrs: adds texture_quality, is_white_model, is_ai_generated, low_confidence\\n  - Uses nvdiff renders from TOS (vs Blender EEVEE in armesh-dev)\\n- HF dataset: `xiyuwang/armesh-dev` (public), ~9.9k/10.25k GLBs uploaded\\n\\n## 2M Annotation Stream — IN PROGRESS\\n- tmux `annotate` on A800-1gpu, Blender EEVEE → 72B fewshot v2 via vLLM\\n- Script: `tools/annotate_stream.py`, output: `data/qwen-anno-72b-fewshot-v2/`\\n- **STOPPED Mar 11** — A800-1gpu node retired by Tim\\n- ~1.3M JSONs done, ~600k SHAs remaining (unannotated)\\n- vLLM backend (A800-dev) still running\\n- 8 attrs: geometry_quality, is_scan, no_semantic, is_closed_mesh, separated_objects, is_scene, has_clean_topology, is_human\\n- Distribution: Keep ~62%, Borderline <1%, Reject ~37%\\n\\n## Annotation History\\n- 72B zero-shot: 10k, 62.8% accept\\n- 27B zero-shot: 10k, ~51% keep\\n- 72B few-shot v1: 1k, too cautious (39.2% keep, 45.5% borderline)\\n- 72B few-shot v2: 1k, **best** (62.9% keep, 1.5% borderline) — now used for 2M stream\\n\\n## DINOv3 Artisan Classifier\\n- DINOv3-ViTS16 + linear head, 5-fold CV on 10,057 samples\\n- Acc 92.3%, F1 95.5%, Prec 94.2%, Recall 97.0%\\n\\n## AR Mesh Architecture Reference\\n- **VAE**: Michelangelo ShapeVAE-256 (MAv2, BPT, MeshMosaic, FastMesh); EdgeRunner uses DummyLatent; TreeMeshGPT uses perceiver\\n- **Condition**: prefix (MAv2, EdgeRunner, FastMesh) vs true cross-attn (BPT, TreeMeshGPT, MeshMosaic)\\n- **Topology**: only EdgeRunner guarantees manifold (half-edge ops); BPT does merge_vertices post-hoc\\n- **Bottleneck**: attention O(n²), not tokenization. BPT at ~1.5 tok/face ≈ 12 bits/face is near-optimal\\n- **Scaling paths**: sparse attention (HiFi-Mesh LANE) or patch decomposition (MeshMosaic)\\n- **EdgeRunner meto**: Edgebreaker-inspired, L/R/BOM ops + parallelogram residuals, state machine enforced at inference\\n- **MeshCraft**: flow-based DiT, 1 tok/face, max 800-1536 faces, 35× faster than MeshGPT but doesn't scale\\n\\n## Manual Annotation Dataset (artistic_scan_index.json)\\n- 3,735 SHAs from rc_wu's dataset (2,508 artistic / 1,227 scan), different source from 2M\\n- CSV: `data/manual_all_shas.csv`\\n- Clean annotation outputs (dedicated dirs, never mix into main pipeline dirs):\\n  - `data/qwen-manual-72b-fewshotv2` — 72B, fewshot v2 prompt, Blender, completed Mar 10\\n  - `data/qwen-manual-27b-toszero` — 27B SparcAI, TOS zero-shot prompt, Blender, completed Mar 10\\n- 27B TOS distribution: Keep 17%, Border 8%, Reject 75% (scan-heavy)\\n- 72B fewshot distribution: Keep 37%, Border 1%, Reject 61%\\n\\n## 27B TOS Annotation — COMPLETE ✅\\n- `qwen-anno-27b-tos`: 1,911,755 files total\\n- Old file_index.csv (1,766,656) + new gap SHAs (344,776 done, 14 failed, 31 skipped)\\n- Final: Keep 29.7%, Borderline 1.4%, Reject 69.0%\\n- 200W CSV SHA col: `sha256_hash` (index 31), 100% TOS wireframe coverage\\n- Sequential distribution: first 100k rows 56% keep, middle stable ~40-42%, last 300k drops to 23-37%\\n\\n## annotate_stream.py — flags added Mar 10\\n- `--zero-shot`: skip fewshot exemplars\\n- `--disable-thinking`: Qwen3 thinking off (`chat_template_kwargs: {enable_thinking: false}`)\\n- `--max-tokens N`: override 512 default\\n- `--tos-prompt`: use TOS zero-shot system prompt instead of fewshot\\n\\n## Gallery Server (A100)\\n- Port 8765, Tailscale: http://100.123.170.90:8765\\n- Merged server v3: manual labeling + multi-model annotations + search/filters/pagination\\n- Scripts: `tools/gallery_server.py` + `tools/gallery_index.html`\\n- Launch: `setsid python3 tools/gallery_server.py --renders data/blender_renders --annotations data/gallery_labels.json --multi-annotations data/qwen_labels_multi.json --manual-labels data/manual_labels.json --port 8765 --host 0.0.0.0 </dev/null &`\\n- Data: 26,888 SHAs with wireframes, 28,092 VLM annotations, 10k multi-model, 185 manual labels\\n- Images: `wireframe_top_left.jpg` (cropped 1536×1536), `wireframe.webp` (full 4608×3072 grid)\\n\\n## Cluster Blender Renders — IN PROGRESS\\n- 16 jobs (42869-42884 + 42886), V100 + Pro6000 nodes\\n- STEP=1131 per job, skip-existing, --requeue, QoS override-limits-but-killable\\n- 16,151/18,092 done (89%) as of Mar 6 7PM\\n- Output: hybrid.jpg + wireframe.jpg per SHA at 1024×1024\\n\\n## New 200W CSV (from Yufei, 2026-03-09)\\n- File: `/dev_vepfs/xiyu/1.csv` (719MB, 2,003,639 records, 48 columns)\\n- Source: `shared-dev/yufei_data/200W_filtered.csv.tar.gz` from BD CPU instance\\n- Key columns: `scanned_prob`, `aesthetic_score_trellis`, `vertex_num`, `has_uvs`, `caption`, `source`\\n- 83% overlap with old file_index.csv; 336k filtered out, 345k new (mostly unlabeled objaverse)\\n- All SHAs have GLBs in TOS bucket (verified 1000/1000)\\n- Sources: 91.2% empty (objaverse), 5.1% sketchfab_trellis, 3.7% github\\n\\n## Manual Labels (rc_wu)\\n- File: `data/artistic_scan_index.json` — 3,735 records (2,508 artistic/67%, 1,227 scan/33%)\\n- Only 20.8% overlap with our 2M dataset — different data source\\n- Agreement: 27B 53.3% (precision 79%, recall 48%), 72B 56.4%\\n- 27B conservative (misses artistic), 72B permissive (lets scan through)\\n\\n## TOS Bucket Structure\\n- `/all-repacked-3d-data/v1/glb/` — full GLB coverage\\n- `v1/wireframe/` — 6-panel webp grid (partial, used by annotate_tos.py)\\n- `v1/nvdiff/{sha}/` — wireframe.jpg + face_normal.jpg (older, broader coverage)\\n- `v1/multi_view_bpy/{sha}/` — rgb.webp + normal_cam.webp 9216×9216 RGBA (newest, partial)\\n- S3 FUSE: must use parallel reads (32+ threads), sequential causes SSH timeouts\\n\\n## BD Internal Network\\n- dev-intern-01: `192.168.0.134` (gateway: 14.103.164.238:2222, user: xiyu.wang)\\n- dev-intern-02: `192.168.0.131` (gateway: 14.103.164.238:2222, user: xiyu.wang)\\n- Root access: `xiyu.wang#root#192.168.0.134` / `192.168.0.131` (root inside container, not host)\\n- **Both are Kubernetes pods** — nvidia-smi shows host PIDs, trust util% not PID list\\n- Co-tenants: liaoyua+, ruochen+, chunyan+, minglin+\\n- A800-dev: RETIRED Mar 12 2026\\n- BD→A100 transfer: only `ssh 'cat file' > local` works (~1.6 MB/s). SCP/rsync/HF all broken.\\n\\n## VAE Overfit Test Results (Mar 19)\\n- **Tiny data** (64 samples, 1430 faces): lr=1e-4 → 99.8% (BD baseline), lr=1e-3 → 92.7%\\n- **Normal data** (64 samples, 121k faces): lr=1e-3 cosine → 78.2% (A100) / 76.7% (BD) — cross-machine verified\\n- CE+bins v1 architecture works, converges, just needs more steps for large face counts\\n- KL=0 for overfit tests (1e-5 causes oscillation at high accuracy)\\n- overfit_test.py: configurable LR, scheduler, KL weight via env vars\\n\\n## Operational Lessons\\n- **NEVER run `du` or `ls` on large/full FUSE filesystems** (VEPFS, S3 mounts). They hang for hours, block the SSH session, and prevent heartbeats from firing (requests-in-flight). Use `stat -f` for free space, `find -maxdepth 1` for top-level listing, or `wc -l` on known files instead.\\n- Read tmux pane for live annotator stats — don't parse 680k+ JSONs (gets OOM killed)\\n- Alpha-transparent webp → JPG: must alpha_composite onto solid bg first, ffmpeg ignores alpha\\n- Gallery process needs setsid + stdin redirect or it dies when parent shell exits\\n- Pro6000 GPU slower than V100 for Blender renders (CPU-bottleneck with 4 CPUs per GPU slot)\\n- CSV with no header + csv.DictReader = silent 0 results (gallery server bug)\\n- git filter-repo purges blobs but removes origin remote — re-add after\\n- Never cancel cluster jobs without Tim's explicit confirmation\\n- `blender_render_glb.py` was lost during git filter-repo purge — backup found in VLMDataClean xiyu-dataclean-dev branch on A100. Now committed to armesh-dev (`7697460`)\\n- RGBA webp → JPG: must alpha_composite onto white bg (not just .convert(\\\"RGB\\\"))\\n- annotate_tos.py field is `annotation.artisan` (not `verdict`) — different schema than expected\\n- When piping Python to remote SSH, variable shadowing with file handles causes silent failures — use unique handle names or write script to file first\\n- Always verify data SHA overlap when comparing runs across machines — different CSVs have different orderings\\n- flex_gemm autotune cache on VEPFS is shared — concurrent writes from multiple processes corrupt it (race condition)\\n- BD has no GitHub SSH key — use `git bundle` relay via A100 for syncing\\n- Local A100 vae env: `source /home/user/miniconda3/bin/activate vae-train` + PYTHONPATH=`third_party/TRELLIS2:armesh-dev`\\n- BD vae env: `conda run -n vae-poc` + PYTHONPATH=`/dev_vepfs/xiyu/armesh-dev:/dev_vepfs/xiyu/trellis2/..`\\n\\n## OpenClaw Notes\\n- Agent routing: `bindings` array in openclaw.json\\n- Heartbeat: 30m interval, monitoring both annotation pipelines + gallery server\\n- Config: `/home/user/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\\n- Model strategy: Opus for heavy thinking/architecture discussion, cheaper models (MiniMax) for routine monitoring/heartbeats to save tokens\\n\\n## Render Speed Benchmark (L40S, Mar 11 2026)\\n- Results: `memory/render-benchmark.md`\\n- Machine: 4× L40S, Blender 5.0.1 EEVEE, smoke500 (500 GLBs ≤4k faces), 1024×1024\\n- **Subprocess per GLB (old baseline)**: 0.35/s (2834ms/model) — cold-start dominated\\n- **Persistent Blender batch (single process)**: 2.07/s — **5.9× faster**\\n- **Sample count**: 64→16 only 6% improvement; 32 samples is sweet spot\\n- **4× parallel workers (1 GPU each)**: 6.5 models/s effective — near-linear scaling\\n- Production for 2M dataset: persistent batch + 4 workers ≈ 51h on L40S (vs ~330h old)\\n- Scripts: `tools/render_fast_eevee.py` (persistent), `tools/bench_render.sh`\\n\\n## Render Speed Benchmark (L40S, Mar 11 2026)\\n- Full results: `memory/render-benchmark.md`\\n- Persistent Blender process vs subprocess: **5.9× faster** (0.48s vs 2.83s/model)\\n- Sample count (64→16): only 6% improvement — not the bottleneck\\n- 4× parallel GPUs (one per L40S): **6.5 models/s** effective, near-linear scaling\\n- Production: persistent batch + 4 workers → 2M models in ~85h on 4×L40S\\n- Script: `tools/render_fast_eevee.py`, benchmark: `tools/bench_render.sh`\\n\\n## Training Preparation\\n- **EdgeRunner first** for smoke test: training code released, meto tokenizer, manifold output\\n- **Smoke500 dataset**: 500 GLBs ≤4k faces (mean 1427, median 1276), all \\\"keep\\\" by 27B\\n  - HF: `xiyuwang/mesh-dev-382620` → `smoke500/`\\n  - Deployed to all 3 machines under `data/smoke-data/`, md5 verified\\n- Face count distribution: ≤4k: 18%, ≤8k: 29%, ≤40k: 72%\\n- Data budget: 50k min viable, 100-200k competitive v1\\n- For v1: use 27B \\\"keep\\\" (high-confidence, 88% agreement with 72B)\\n\\n## HF Dataset\\n- Repo: `xiyuwang/xiyuwang-armesh-dev-31826` (public, created Mar 18 — old `mesh-dev-382620` deleted)\\n- Old repo `xiyuwang/armesh-dev` deleted by Tim (Mar 10)\\n- Token in `.bashrc` on all 3 machines; A800: `HF_ENDPOINT=https://hf-mirror.com`\\n- NTU cluster: `module load Miniforge3/24.11.3-1 && source activate base`\\n- manual-anno upload in progress (tmux `hf-upload` on A800-1gpu): GLBs + renders + annotations for 3,735 SHAs\\n\\n## Video Annotation (experimental, Mar 10)\\n- 27B SparcAI accepts video input (base64 mp4 via `video_url` type)\\n- ~9× more prompt tokens vs single image (11,959 vs 1,284)\\n- Turntable render: 150 frames too slow (~15 min/model), need single-session Blender script\\n\\n## Cross-Model Agreement (Full, 947k overlap)\\n- Agreement: 67.6% — Both keep 39.1%, Both reject 28.5%\\n- 27B keep/72B reject: 5.5%, 27B reject/72B keep: 24.1%\\n- 27B \\\"keep\\\" is high-confidence (88% 72B agrees)\\n\\n## Human vs VLM Agreement (3,735 manual samples from rc_wu)\\n- Human vs 72B: 49.1% agreement — 72B over-rejects artistic (1,463/2,508 = 58%)\\n- Human vs 27B: 42.3% agreement — 27B even more conservative (1,726/2,508 = 69% rejected)\\n- Root cause: VLMs judge geometric quality/structure, not provenance (scan vs artistic)\\n- Human-scan but both models keep: 97 SHAs (clean scans that look \\\"intentional\\\")\\n- Human-artistic, no VLM agrees: 56.9% — VLM prompts too strict for rc_wu's definition\\n\\n## Research Direction — Artisan Mesh Generation\\n- Tim's plan: `plans/big-plan.md` — scaffold → compact AR → refinement → quality enforcement\\n- Key papers in `papers/`: QuadGPT, Mesh-Pro, MeshRipple, Eval3D, ArtUV, NeuFrameQ, HiFiMesh, **LATO**\\n- Field converging on RL post-training (tDPO/ARPO/GRPO) for topology\\n- Hardest: scaffold representation, scaffold→mesh gap, eval protocol\\n- Critical decision pending: triangle-first vs quad-first\\n- Metrics analysis: `plans/artisan-metrics-analysis.md`\\n\\n### LATO (Mar 2026) — Key Competitor / Inspiration\\n- Sparse voxel VAE + flow matching (NOT AR, NOT implicit SDF) — third paradigm\\n- Vertex Displacement Field: 819k surface points → 9D displacements to face vertices → voxelize → T-Voxels\\n- Decoder: hierarchical subdivide-and-prune (3× 8-way), connection head predicts edges between vertex pairs\\n- Two-stage flow matching: structure voxels → topology features\\n- Beats all AR methods (BPT, DeepMesh, etc.), 3-10s inference, handles open/non-manifold\\n- 400k assets, 8×H100, 4d VAE + 7d flow matching\\n- Our VAE approach is conceptually similar (vertex offsets from voxel anchors) — LATO validates the direction\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:17:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_8\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The required context is loaded except the daily notes command, which failed on quoting. I’m fixing that and then searching the codebase for the center-head and proposal-attention implementation so the memory estimates are grounded in actual tensor shapes.\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:18:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"center head|center_head|proposal attention|proposal_attention|proposal attn|centerhead|proposal_attn|K_g|num_proposals|num_queries|topk|gaussian\\\" -S .'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:19:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"center head|center_head|proposal attention|proposal_attention|proposal attn|centerhead|proposal_attn|K_g|num_proposals|num_queries|topk|gaussian\\\" -S .'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/bin/bash: line 1: rg: command not found\\n\",\"exit_code\":127,\"status\":\"failed\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log:22:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_10\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' METADATA.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# METADATA.md — Quick Reference\\n\\nRead this first. Don't read scripts unless you need to modify them.\\n\\n## Directory Layout\\n\\n```\\narmesh-dev/\\n├── bpt/                        # BPT mesh tokenization + training\\n│   ├── pretokenize.py          # Convert GLBs → BPT token sequences\\n│   └── train.py                # Train BPT mesh generation model\\n├── tools/                      # Operational scripts (data pipeline + serving)\\n│   ├── annotate_stream.py      # 2M VLM annotation pipeline (runs on A800-1gpu)\\n│   │                           #   Blender EEVEE render → Qwen2.5-VL-72B via vLLM (TP8, local)\\n│   │                           #   8 attrs, few-shot, output: JSON per SHA in data/qwen-anno-72b-fewshot-v2/\\n│   ├── annotate_tos.py         # Lightweight TOS-based annotator (runs on A800-dev)\\n│   │                           #   3-stage: fetch (shutil.copy2→/dev/shm) → decode (PIL ProcessPool) → annotate (HTTP)\\n│   │                           #   Fixed views: right side + front (was random), 1024×1024 JPEG (was 768×768)\\n│   │                           #   Queries Qwen3.5-27B via SparcAI vLLM, max_tokens=2048\\n│   │                           #   Filters: poor geometry, scattered wires, trivial shapes, multi-object\\n│   │                           #   Output: JSON per SHA in data/qwen-anno-27b-tos/\\n│   │                           #   Config: --fetch-workers 64 --decode-workers 32 --annotate-workers 48, rate ~6.7/s\\n│   ├── crop_wireframes.py      # Crop wireframe.webp (4608×3072 6-view grid) → wireframe_top_left.jpg (1536×1536)\\n│   │                           #   Alpha-composites onto black bg, ProcessPoolExecutor\\n│   ├── gallery_server.py       # ThreadingHTTPServer with manual labeling API (fcntl locking)\\n│   │                           #   CLI: --renders --annotations --multi-annotations --manual-labels --port --host\\n│   ├── gallery_index.html      # Gallery UI: search, filters, pagination, lightbox, multi-model annotation tags\\n│   ├── stage_wireframes.py     # Stage wireframe.webp from TOS to local dir (parallel reads)\\n│   │                           #   CLI: --index --src --dst --workers\\n│   ├── render_exemplars.sh     # Render few-shot exemplar images for annotation prompts\\n│   ├── render_blender/\\n│   │   ├── run_render_batch.py         # Cluster Blender batch renderer (generic, CLI args)\\n│   │   │                               #   Parallel subprocesses, skip-existing, SSD tmp dir\\n│   │   └── render_gallery_cluster.sbatch  # Slurm sbatch wrapper for cluster submission\\n│   └── prompts/                # VLM annotation prompts (per model variant)\\n│       ├── default.txt\\n│       ├── qwen2.5-vl-72b.txt\\n│       ├── qwen3.5-27b.txt\\n│       ├── qwen3.5-27b-v2.txt # ← v2 few-shot prompt (used for 2M stream)\\n│       └── qwen3.5-moe.txt\\n├── third_party/                # Reference repos (source snapshots, no .git dirs)\\n│   └── (11 repos: bpt, dinov3_core, EdgeRunner, FastMesh, Hunyuan3D-2.1,\\n│        MeshAnythingV2, MeshCraft, MeshMosaic, MeshRipple, TreeMeshGPT, TRELLIS2)\\n├── train/                      # Training artifacts (DINOv3 classifier runs)\\n├── data/                       # All data (gitignored, large)\\n│   ├── blender_renders/<sha>/  # 28,092 dirs: wireframe.webp + wireframe_top_left.jpg\\n│   ├── gallery_labels.json     # 28,092 VLM annotations {sha: {artisan, quality, confidence}}\\n│   ├── qwen_labels_multi.json  # 10k multi-model annotations {sha: {model: {artisan, reasoning, attrs...}}}\\n│   ├── manual_labels.json      # Human labels from gallery labeling UI {sha: {artisan, quality}}\\n│   ├── manual-label/           # Old 10k annotation outputs (qwen-anno-72b/, qwen-anno-27b/)\\n│   └── gallery_index.csv       # Old SHA list (headerless, superseded by dir scan)\\n├── papers/                     # Downloaded research papers\\n├── docs/                       # OpenClaw docs mirror\\n├── memory/                     # Daily memory + heartbeat state\\n├── SOUL.md                     # Who I am, how I work\\n├── MEMORY.md                   # Long-term memory (curated)\\n├── TOOLS.md                    # SSH hosts, running servers, infra notes\\n├── USER.md                     # About Tim\\n├── HEARTBEAT.md                # Periodic check tasks\\n└── METADATA.md                 # This file\\n```\\n\\n## Data Formats\\n\\n**VLM annotation JSON** (per SHA, on A800):\\n```json\\n{\\\"sha256\\\": \\\"abc...\\\", \\\"annotation\\\": {\\\"artisan\\\": \\\"keep\\\", \\\"confidence\\\": 0.92, \\\"quality\\\": \\\"high\\\",\\n  \\\"geometry_quality\\\": \\\"high\\\", \\\"is_scan\\\": false, \\\"no_semantic\\\": false, \\\"is_closed_mesh\\\": true,\\n  \\\"separated_objects\\\": false, \\\"is_scene\\\": false, \\\"has_clean_topology\\\": true, \\\"is_human\\\": false},\\n \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {...}, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n**TOS annotator JSON** (per SHA, on A800-dev, `data/qwen-anno-27b-tos/`):\\n```json\\n{\\\"sha256\\\": \\\"abc...\\\", \\\"annotation\\\": {\\\"artisan\\\": \\\"keep\\\"|\\\"reject\\\", \\\"confidence\\\": 0.0-1.0,\\n  \\\"quality\\\": \\\"high\\\"|\\\"medium\\\"|\\\"low\\\", \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"1 sentence\\\",\\n  \\\"geometry_quality\\\", \\\"is_scan\\\", \\\"no_semantic\\\", \\\"is_closed_mesh\\\",\\n  \\\"separated_objects\\\", \\\"is_scene\\\", \\\"has_clean_topology\\\", \\\"is_human\\\"},\\n \\\"usage\\\": {...}, \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n**gallery_labels.json**: `{sha: {artisan: \\\"keep\\\"|\\\"reject\\\"|\\\"borderline\\\", quality, confidence}}`\\n**qwen_labels_multi.json**: `{sha: {\\\"qwen2.5-vl-72b\\\": {...}, \\\"qwen3.5-27b\\\": {...}, \\\"72b-fewshot-v2\\\": {...}}}`\\n**manual_labels.json**: `{sha: {artisan: true|false, quality: \\\"high\\\"|\\\"medium\\\"|\\\"low\\\"}}`\\n\\n## Active Annotation Pipelines\\n\\n| Pipeline | Machine | Model | Backend | Rate | ETA | Output |\\n|----------|---------|-------|---------|------|-----|--------|\\n| `annotate_stream.py` | A800-1gpu (tmux `annotate`) | Qwen2.5-VL-72B | Local vLLM TP8 | ~1.6/s | ~8 days | `data/qwen-anno-72b-fewshot-v2/` |\\n| `annotate_tos.py` | A800-dev (tmux `annotate-tos`) | Qwen3.5-27B | SparcAI vLLM | ~6.7/s | ~2.5 days | `data/qwen-anno-27b-tos/` |\\n\\n## Key Image Paths\\n\\n- TOS wireframe: `/all-repacked-3d-data/v1/wireframe/<sha>/wireframe.webp` (4608×3072, 6-view)\\n- Local render: `data/blender_renders/<sha>/wireframe_top_left.jpg` (1536×1536, cropped)\\n- Cluster render: `/projects/_ssd/xiyu004var/armesh-dev/data/blender_renders/<sha>/hybrid.jpg` + `wireframe.jpg` (1024×1024)\\n\\n## Gallery Server Launch\\n\\n```bash\\nsetsid python3 tools/gallery_server.py \\\\\\n  --renders data/blender_renders \\\\\\n  --annotations data/gallery_labels.json \\\\\\n  --multi-annotations data/qwen_labels_multi.json \\\\\\n  --manual-labels data/manual_labels.json \\\\\\n  --port 8765 --host 0.0.0.0 \\\\\\n  </dev/null > logs/gallery_server.log 2>&1 &\\n```\\n\\n## Git\\n\\n- Repo: `TimandXiyu/armesh-dev.git`, branch `main`\\n- `data/`, `third_party/`, `papers/`, `docs/`, `config/`, `skills/` are gitignored\\n- `.git` is 4.5MB (purged history with git-filter-repo)\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/dev_vepfs/rc_wu/codex_subagents/20260328_mesh_center_wave2/memory-guardrails/stdout.log: